The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Ispat net profit jumps to Rs 34.8cr
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       Ispat net profit jumps to Rs 34.8cr
          OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                      NUMBER GAME                          
	Calcutta, July 2: Pramod and Vinod Mittal-owned Ispat Industries Ltd has posted a net profit of Rs 34.80 crore for the 12-month period ended March 31, 2008, against a net loss of Rs 9.53 crore for the corresponding period of the previous year.        
	Ispats profit before tax improved to Rs 115.62 crore in 2007-08 from Rs 3.37 crore in the previous fiscal.        
	The companys total income in 2007-08 grew 14.59 per cent to Rs 8,711 crore from Rs 7,602.20 crore a year ago.         
	For the fourth quarter ended March 31, 2008, Ispats net profit dipped to Rs 48.89 crore from Rs 82.12 crore in the corresponding quarter of the previous year.         
	The company reported a fall in profit before tax at Rs 78.84 crore during the fourth quarter compared with Rs 134.04 crore in the year-ago period. The total income during the fourth quarter of 2007-8 at Rs 2,600.52 crore was higher by 21.31 per cent compared with the same period a year ago.        
	Ramsarup on track        
	Ramsarup Industries Ltd, one of the largest producers of steel wires, registered a 36 per cent rise in net profit at Rs 59.42 crore for the year ended March 31, 2008, against Rs 43.56 crore in the previous fiscal.        
	Exports jumped to Rs 95.73 crore from Rs 71.44 crore a year ago.        
	The net income during 2007-08 stood at Rs 1,581.85 crore, up 21 per cent from Rs 1,306.02 crore in the previous fiscal. Wire and steel products continue to be growth drivers for the company.         
	The order for the multi product plating line plant is on course and is expected to start production in the current year. The company is targeting six lakh metres of steel wires and finished wire products by 2010.                                                                                                                                     
